&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smriti Mandhana.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smriti Mandhana was named BBC Indian Sportswoman of the Year for 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smriti Mandhana&lt;/strong&gt; played a pivotal role in India&amp;rsquo;s historic 2025 Women&amp;rsquo;s World Cup triumph.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The award recognises her outstanding performance in international cricket during 2025.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;She became one of the most prolific batters of the year, contributing significantly to India&amp;rsquo;s success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The recognition highlights her impact on women&amp;rsquo;s cricket at both national and global levels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BBC Indian Sportswoman of the Year:&lt;/strong&gt; An annual award presented by the BBC to recognise the most outstanding female athlete from India based on performance and achievement during the year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smriti Mandhana:&lt;/strong&gt; A left-handed batter known for her elegant strokeplay and consistent run-scoring across formats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2025 Achievements:&lt;/strong&gt; Contributed to India&amp;rsquo;s Women&amp;rsquo;s World Cup victory and maintained a high level of international performance throughout the year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance:&lt;/strong&gt; The award highlights the growing influence and success of women athletes in Indian sport.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;One Battle After Another&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Michael Bauman won the Best Cinematography award for his stunning visual work in &lt;strong&gt;One Battle After Another&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This was one of the two technical/craft awards the film won, alongside Best Editing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

