		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;Best Adapted Screenplay:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;25&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;Paul Thomas Anderson&lt;/b&gt; for &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;50&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;50&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;One Battle After Another&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;Best Children&amp;#39;s &amp;amp; Family Film:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;31&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;31&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;Boong&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;. Backed by Excel Entertainment, this Manipuri-language film made history as the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;117&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;first Indian film&lt;/b&gt; to win a BAFTA in this category.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,3,0&quot;&gt;Best Animated Film:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;20&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;20&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,3,0&quot;&gt;Zootopia 2&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,4,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,4,0&quot;&gt;Best Film Not in the English Language:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;39&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,4,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;39&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,4,0&quot;&gt;Sentimental Value&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,5,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,5,0&quot;&gt;Best Documentary:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;18&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,5,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;18&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,5,0&quot;&gt;Mr Nobody Against Putin&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot;&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Special Honors&lt;/b&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;Technical Sweeps:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;18&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;18&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;Frankenstein&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; won three awards for &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;52&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;Production Design&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;71&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;Costume Design&lt;/b&gt;, and &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;91&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;Make Up &amp;amp; Hair&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;Best Original Score:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;21&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;Ludwig G&amp;ouml;ransson&lt;/b&gt; for &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;42&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;42&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;Sinners&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; (Ryan Coogler accepted the award on his behalf, joking he was busy with &amp;quot;a small independent film called &lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;155&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;The Odyssey&lt;/i&gt;&amp;quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;9,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,2,0&quot;&gt;Best Sound:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;12&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;12&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,2,0&quot;&gt;F1&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;9,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,3,0&quot;&gt;Best Special Visual Effects:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;29&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;29&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,3,0&quot;&gt;Avatar: Fire and Ash&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;9,4,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,4,0&quot;&gt;BAFTA Fellowship:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;18&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,4,0&quot;&gt;Donna Langley&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;9,5,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,5,0&quot;&gt;Outstanding British Contribution to Cinema:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;44&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9,5,0&quot;&gt;Clare Binns&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;Historic Milestones&lt;/b&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,0&quot;&gt;One Battle After Another&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; set a BAFTA record for the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;52&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,0&quot;&gt;most nominations (14)&lt;/b&gt; and led the night with &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;97&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,0&quot;&gt;6 wins&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,0&quot;&gt;Hamnet&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; became the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;18&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,0&quot;&gt;most-nominated film by a female director&lt;/b&gt; (Chlo&amp;eacute; Zhao) in BAFTA history with 11 nominations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;11,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,2,0&quot;&gt;Sinners&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; became the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;19&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,2,0&quot;&gt;most-nominated and most-awarded film by a Black director&lt;/b&gt; (Ryan Coogler), earning 13 nominations and 3 wins.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;11,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,3,0&quot;&gt;Marty Supreme&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; tied the record for the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;38&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11,3,0&quot;&gt;most losses&lt;/b&gt; at a single ceremony, going 0-for-11.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India set a new &lt;strong&gt;Guinness World Record in 2025&lt;/strong&gt; for the largest human formation of the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt;, a symbol of peace, dharma, and progress.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The event took place with the participation of thousands of people who came together to form the intricate design of the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt;, which is featured prominently on the Indian national flag.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt; consists of 24 spokes, representing the 24 virtues such as love, courage, patience, and righteousness, which are significant in Indian cultural and philosophical heritage.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This record-breaking event was organized to promote unity, patriotism, and the values that the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt; symbolizes in Indian society.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Guinness World Record team verified the formation&amp;#39;s accuracy and adherence to the dimensions of the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt; as depicted on the national flag.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt; is derived from the Lion Capital of Ashoka at Sarnath, which is one of the most prominent symbols of India&amp;#39;s rich heritage.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It represents the &lt;strong&gt;wheel of dharma&lt;/strong&gt;, embodying the principles of truth, justice, and progress.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The 24 spokes in the chakra symbolize the life cycle and virtues essential for maintaining harmony and balance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is prominently displayed in the center of the &lt;strong&gt;Indian national flag&lt;/strong&gt;, signifying motion and dynamism.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance of Guinness World Records:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Guinness World Records is an internationally recognized authority for documenting extraordinary feats and achievements.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India has consistently set records in various domains, showcasing its cultural, social, and scientific achievements.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Events like the formation of the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt; highlight the nation&amp;#39;s unity and collective spirit.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Notable Symbols:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heart Shape:&lt;/strong&gt; Globally recognized as a symbol of love and compassion.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Olympic Rings:&lt;/strong&gt; Representing the unity of five continents and the Olympic spirit.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Peace Symbol:&lt;/strong&gt; Widely used to signify harmony and the absence of conflict.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Historical Context of the Ashoka Chakra:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The chakra is named after &lt;strong&gt;Emperor Ashoka&lt;/strong&gt;, one of India&amp;#39;s greatest rulers, who embraced Buddhism and propagated values of peace and dharma.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a reminder of India&amp;#39;s commitment to universal values and moral principles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guinness World Record Verification:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The record-breaking formation required precise planning and execution to accurately depict the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Participants were trained to understand the design and significance of the symbol.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Such events foster patriotism and are a celebration of India&amp;#39;s national identity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role of Symbols in National Identity:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Symbols like the &lt;strong&gt;Ashoka Chakra&lt;/strong&gt; play a pivotal role in expressing the ethos and values of a nation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are used in national events, government documents, and cultural representations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Educational programs often emphasize their importance to instill respect and pride in citizens.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;150 Hours.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Directorate General of Training (DGT) has mandated 150 hours of On-the-Job Training (OJT) or Group Projects for all ITI trainees under the Craftsmen Training Scheme (CTS).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The reform is effective from the academic session 2022&amp;ndash;23 and applies to all Industrial Training Institutes (ITIs) nationwide.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Trainees become eligible for this 150-hour requirement after completing at least three months of their regular ITI training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The move reduces campus-based training from 1,600 hours to 1,200 hours annually to allow for more direct industry exposure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Implementation Options&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Primary Option - OJT in partnered industries under the guidance of industry mentors.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Alternative Option - A trade-related Group Project, to be undertaken if a physical OJT placement is not feasible.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;DGT (Directorate General of Training)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Parent Ministry - Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Role - The apex organization for development and coordination of programs relating to vocational training in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Craftsmen Training Scheme (CTS)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launch Year - 1950.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Objective - To ensure a steady flow of skilled workers in different trades for domestic industry and to reduce unemployment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;National Education Policy (NEP) 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Connection - The ITI reform aligns with NEP 2020&amp;rsquo;s goal of integrating vocational education with mainstream education and emphasizing practical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Skill India Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Vision - Launched in 2015 to create a &amp;quot;swarozgar&amp;quot; (self-reliant) youth workforce through various skill development initiatives like PMKVY and CTS.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Layer, AI Model Layer, Compute Layer, Data Centres and Network Infrastructure Layer, Energy Layer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The India AI Stack is structured into five distinct layers that collectively enable development, deployment, and scaling of AI systems across sectors.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The India AI Stack consists of exactly five layers: Application Layer, AI Model Layer, Compute Layer, Data Centres and Network Infrastructure Layer, and Energy Layer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These layers together provide the full ecosystem required for building, deploying, and scaling AI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Data Centres and Network Infrastructure Layer combines both storage and connectivity, making it a single integrated layer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Energy Layer ensures reliable electricity supply, enabling continuous operation of compute systems and AI infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Stack&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;An AI stack is the complete set of technologies required to develop, deploy, and operate AI applications.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It integrates software, hardware, infrastructure, and energy systems.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It ensures scalable, reliable, and population-scale deployment of AI.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compute Layer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Provides computational power through GPUs, TPUs, and NPUs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Supports training and execution of AI models.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Determines speed, efficiency, and scalability of AI systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Centres and Network Infrastructure Layer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Acts as the backbone of AI deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Stores AI data, models, and enables real-time connectivity.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Includes broadband, cloud systems, and 5G networks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Energy Layer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Provides electricity required to operate AI infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Supports data centres, servers, and computing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ensures sustainable and uninterrupted AI operations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shibnote, Doda.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 6th National Rafting Championship titled &amp;ldquo;The Ultimate River Battle&amp;rdquo;inaugurated at Shibnote in Doda district of Jammu and Kashmir.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The championship was organised (19th to 22nd February 2026) on the Chenab River, known for its challenging rapids.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The event aims to promote adventure tourism and position Jammu &amp;amp; Kashmir as a premier adventure sports destination.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a four-day national-level sporting event.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The event is organised by the J&amp;amp;K Tourism Department in collaboration with the Doda District Administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chenab River:&lt;/strong&gt; One of the major rivers of the Indus system, known for its fast-flowing currents and suitability for rafting competitions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Doda District:&lt;/strong&gt; An emerging hub for eco-tourism and water sports in Jammu &amp;amp; Kashmir.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alexander Stubb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief Guest:&lt;/strong&gt; The President of Finland, &lt;strong&gt;Alexander Stubb&lt;/strong&gt;, served as the Chief Guest for the &lt;strong&gt;11th edition of the Raisina Dialogue&lt;/strong&gt; held in New Delhi in March 2026 (5th to 7th March).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keynote Address:&lt;/strong&gt; President Stubb delivered the inaugural keynote address, emphasizing the importance of &lt;strong&gt;multilateralism&lt;/strong&gt; and the role of the &amp;quot;Global North&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Global South&amp;quot; in navigating a fractured world order.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theme:&lt;/strong&gt; The theme of the 2026 edition is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Saṁskāra &amp;ndash; Assertion, Accommodation, Advancement&amp;rdquo;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Six thematic pillars:&lt;/strong&gt; (i) Contested Frontiers: Power, Polarity, and Periphery; (ii) Repairing the Commons: New Groups, New Guardians, New Avenues; (iii) White Whale: The Pursuit of Agenda 2030; (iv) The Eleventh Hour: Climate, Conflict, and the Cost of Delay; (v) Tomorrowland: Towards a Tech-topia; (vi) Trade in the Time of Tariffs: Recovery, Resilience, Reinvention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Highlights of the Event&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organizers:&lt;/strong&gt; The conference is India&amp;rsquo;s flagship conference on geopolitics and geo-economics, hosted by the &lt;strong&gt;Observer Research Foundation (ORF)&lt;/strong&gt; in collaboration with the &lt;strong&gt;Ministry of External Affairs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nordic Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; The presence of the Finnish President highlighted India&amp;#39;s strengthening ties with &lt;strong&gt;Nordic-Baltic countries&lt;/strong&gt;, particularly in areas of green energy, technology, and security.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Participation:&lt;/strong&gt; The 2026 dialogue saw participation from over 100 countries, including ministers, former heads of state, and technology leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;About Raisina Dialogue&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inception:&lt;/strong&gt; Launched in &lt;strong&gt;2016&lt;/strong&gt;, the Raisina Dialogue has quickly become one of the most prominent global forums for discussing international relations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format:&lt;/strong&gt; It is designed as a multi-stakeholder, cross-sectoral discussion, involving heads of state, cabinet ministers, and local government officials, as well as thought leaders from the private sector and media.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Venue:&lt;/strong&gt; It is traditionally held in &lt;strong&gt;New Delhi&lt;/strong&gt;, taking its name from Raisina Hill, the seat of the Government of India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

